<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  Korean (`ko`) string overrides. The Android resource system
  picks this file for any device whose primary locale resolves to
  Korean (`ko`, `ko-rKR`, `ko-rKP`); every other locale falls back
  to the canonical English copy in `values/strings.xml`.

  Pairing additions: when adding a new translatable string, add the
  English copy in `values/strings.xml` first, then the Korean
  rendering here. Keep the resource name identical between both
  files. Format placeholders (%1$s, %1$d, %%, etc.) and escaped
  glyphs are preserved verbatim — translators only adjust the
  surrounding prose.

  A small set of strings is intentionally NOT translated:
    * `app_name`, contributor display names, brand-y labels
      ("Quick Share", "bada") — proper nouns.
    * `credit_teqhnikacross_desc` — the contributor explicitly
      asked for "We all want to be loved" rendered as-is on Korean
      devices too.

  `credit_yeonfeel_desc` and `credit_thanks_compact` used to be left
  Korean-in-canonical; both are now fully localized (English canonical,
  Korean here, Japanese in values-ja). For `credit_thanks_compact` only
  the parenthetical contribution note is translated — "Chiyak" stays.
-->
